      • ACTION_ENTER_TIP

        public static final java.lang.String ACTION_ENTER_TIP
        Activity Action: Enter Tip
        "com.pax.us.pay.action.ENTER_TIP"

        Input: EntryExtraData.PARAM_PACKAGE - is the package name of caller.
        Type: String

        Input: EntryExtraData.PARAM_TRANS_TYPE - is transaction name. Example: "CREDIT SALE"

        Input: EntryExtraData.PARAM_TRANS_MODE - is transaction mode.
        Type: String
        See TransMode for details

        Input: EntryExtraData.PARAM_TIMEOUT -
        Type: Long
        Unit: ms
        Default is 30000.
        For reference only, BroadPOS handles timeout.

        Input: EntryExtraData.PARAM_CURRENCY - is currency type.
        Type: String
        Default value: CurrencyType.USD

        Input: EntryExtraData.PARAM_BASE_AMOUNT -
        Type: Long

        Input: EntryExtraData.PARAM_TIP_NAME -
        Type: String
        Default value is "Tip"
        In BroadPOS standalone mode, if multiple tips are enabled, value might be "Tip1", "Tip2", or any value configured by merchant

        Input: EntryExtraData.PARAM_TIP_OPTIONS - is tip options. Type: String[]
        It is optional. Used when tip select is enabled.

        Example:
        if value of EntryExtraData.PARAM_TIP_OPTIONS is {"300","500","700"},
        you could provide 3 options for user:

        $3.00, $5.00, $7.00

        Input: EntryExtraData.PARAM_TIP_RATE_OPTIONS - is tip percentage options.
        Type: String[]
        It is optional. Used when tip select is enabled.
        Used with EntryExtraData.PARAM_TIP_OPTIONS together.

        Example:
        if value of EntryExtraData.PARAM_TIP_OPTIONS is {"1000","1500","1800"} and value of EntryExtraData.PARAM_TIP_RATE_OPTIONS is {"10","15","18"},
        you could provide 3 options for user:

        $10.00(10%), $15.00(15%), $18.00(18%)

        Input: EntryExtraData.PARAM_TIP_UNIT - .
        Type: String
        Default is "C".

        Input: EntryExtraData.PARAM_AMOUNT_UNIT -
        Type: Long
        Deprecated. Not used anymore. Use EntryExtraData.PARAM_TIP_UNIT instead.

        Input: EntryExtraData.PARAM_VALUE_PATTERN - is length limit.
        Type: String
        Default: "0-12". It is used for manual input tip.

        Input: EntryExtraData.PARAM_TIP_NAMES -
        Type: String[]
        Name of Enabled Tips
        Optional. For Standalone use only. Used when multiple tips are enabled.

        Input: EntryExtraData.PARAM_TIP_AMOUNTS -
        Type: String[]
        Value of Enabled Tips
        Optional. For Standalone use only. Used when multiple tips are enabled.

        Example:
        If TIP1, TIP2, TIP3 are all enabled.
        If name of enabled tips is: {"TIP", "TIP2", "TIP3}
        value of enabled tips is: {"100", "200"}
        That means:
        The customer has entered $1.00 TIP, $2.00 TIP2. TIP3 not valued yet.

        Input: EntryExtraData.PARAM_ENABLE_NO_TIP_SELECTION -
        Type: Boolean
        Optional. TRUE means NO TIP SELECTION is enabled.

        Output: EntryRequest.PARAM_TIP -
        Type: Long
        Optional.
        If return nothing, BroadPOS will treat it as tip bypassed.
        If return 0, BroadPOS will treat it as "NO TIP"

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
